item.title: CVE-2021-23845|2024-09-16T21:57:38.685Z -- bosch -- b426%20firmware
item.description: This vulnerability could allow an attacker to hijack a session while a user is logged in the configuration web page. This vulnerability was discovered by a security researcher in B426 and found during internal product tests in B426-CN/B429-CN, and B426-M and has been fixed already starting from version 3.08 on, which was released on June 2019.
